rComments: John's a great guy and he always offers to help out his students. The course itself has way too many readings for a bird course and the tests' grading criteria are hard to get used to.

He made lectures so engaging that I made all of my 9am lectures (and stayed awake through them)! Also he's clearly invested in the subject and in the students, and overall is so so sweet. Listens to student feedback and adjusts course accordingly.

Okay, so, even though I almost failed Latin101, I would still recommend John as a professor. He is the ONLY reason I passed this class. He was the most helpful professor I have ever had at any university, and he is just the sweetest man. Seriously, if you ever find yourself taking LAT101, take it with John.

BEST prof I have ever had at UofT... not sure how his other courses go, but if you have the chance to take CLA201 in the summer with MacCormick, go for it; you will not regret it. Very knowledgeable man, applies worldly stuff to his material. Polite and funny! Study hard and you'll get an A++ no doubt. I wish this man could teach me all my courses!
